# Examining Two-Way and Nested Selection 

#### Let's take a look at some things that might have stood out to you in the previous level.

---

## Two-way Selection

<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px; padding: 20px;">
        
        <div style="background-color: #F7F8FA; padding: 20px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2); border-radius: 8px;">
        <p style = "font-size: 14pt">
        One of the conditional blocks <b>will</b> run: 
        </p>
             <ul>
                <li style = "font-size: 14pt">If <b>True</b> ,the code inside the <code>if</code> block runs</li><br>
                <li style = "font-size: 14pt">If <b>False</b> ,the code inside the <code>else</code> block runs</li>
             </ul>
        </div>

       
<div>
            <img src="https://images.code.org/f652127f4b37d7e8ebf1749a9efda6e9-image-1741709675258.png" alt text= "code depicting an if/else selection statement" style="border-radius: 8px;">
        </div>
    </div>

